frameDefinitions: This frame contains words referring to teaching and the participants in teaching.
This frame describes means actions (Preparatory_acts) that are taken by an Agent for the purpose of preparing for a later act.
A Protagonist comes to suffer from a Disease, often implicitly acquired from a Source.
An Agent enacts an Action that is intended to be performed again at one or more later Occasions.
A Feature of an Entity serves to distinguish the Entity from other members of its type which have a different value for the Feature.
An Agent prepares for an Activity. ''
frameExamples: Dad <t>taught</t> me that if you work hard, you will be OK - no matter what happens.
This update lays the <t>groundwork</t> for future improvements.
I <t>practiced</t> my song for the play.
His <t>distinctive</t> flowing gait and skill with the rapier set him apart from his fellows.
The troops were <t>preparing</t> themselves for the mission.
listRoleDefinitions: One who instructs a <fen>Student</fen> in some area of knowledge or skill.
One who is instructed by a <fen>Teacher</fen> in skills or knowledge.
An educational establishment, such as a school or college.
The area of knowledge or skill which is taught by a <fen>Teacher</fen> or to a <fen>Student</fen>.
A formal Qualification such as an academic degree or a certificate for which a student is aiming.
An action which the <fen>Student</fen> is able to perform as a result of instruction.
A guideline for correct behavior. In most cases, this concerns morally or socially desirable actions.
A piece of information that the <fen>Student</fen> is informed of by the <fen>Teacher</fen>.
Educational <fen>Material</fen>, such as books, tapes, or videos, used by a <fen>Teacher</fen> or a <fen>Student</fen> to acquire skills or knowledge.
A role, typically professional or vocational,  that the <fen>Student</fen> is meant to be able to fill as a result of their training.
FN: a program of lectures or other matter dealing with a subject
The time when the teaching occurs.

The <fen>Place</fen> is the location within which the teaching takes place.

Consider whether a possible <fen>Place</fen> phrase is really where the training took place or is rather part of a description of the <fen>Institution</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> uses the <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> to acheive a <fen>Purpose</fen>.
The action performed by the Agent that is a preliminary to the achievement of the <fen>Purpose</fen>. The <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> may also be expressed by a result of such an act.
The ultimate goal or purpose of the <fen>Agent</fen>, which the Preparatory_act enables.
The part of the larger process that is preliminary to the achievement of the <fen>Purpose</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> takes place.
The place where the <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> takes place.
The time at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> contracts the <fen>Disease</fen>.

The location at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> contracts the <fen>Disease</fen>.  It is different from the <fen>Source</fen> (usually marked with 'from') in that it does not necessarily mean that it was contact with the <fen>Place</fen> that actually led to infection.
This role identifies the <fen>Action</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally in order to prepare for a later <fen>Occasion</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the <fen>Action</fen> in preparation for later performances of the same type.
The later enactment or enactments that the <fen>Agent</fen> expects to perform. Note that the <fen>Agent</fen> does not have to have specific <fen>Occasion</fen>s in mind.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> practices.
This role identifies the place where the practicing occurs.
The aspect of the <fen>Entity</fen> which makes it different from the other members of its class.
The item which differs from other members of its class in the <fen>Feature</fen>'s value.
An <fen>Agent</fen> prepares for an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> for which an <fen>Agent</fen> is preparing.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which an <fen>Agent</fen> prepares for an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where an <fen>Agent</fen> prepares for an <fen>Activity</fen>.
listRoleExamples: Taut with worry, Dad taught us <fex>how to drive</fex>.
My brother taught me <fex>not to be mean to guys when I'm not interested in them</fex>.
When I was two she taught me <fex>that a quarter was 25 cents and a dime was 10 cents</fex>.
All employees have received <fex>a booklet</fex> INSTRUCTING them on how to report ` anything from unwanted touching and uncalled-for blue jokes to overt demands for sexual favours . '
When his father died he went to live with an uncle in Ka'u who trained him <fex>as a warrior</fex> during his teenage years
<fex>The company's actions at that stage</fex> were simply preliminary to the takeover.
We are still in the preliminary <fex>phases</fex>.
Little Dieter practiced <fex>playing the piano</fex> all day.
<fex>For our brother's wedding</fex> we had to rehearse the dinner twenty times.
Our band practices <fex>on the football field</fex>.
That never depleting ammo in his arsenal - his signature <fex>smile</fex> - is contagious.
These signatures may be distinctive <fex>of the entire Chlamydiales order</fex>.
